# Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values. Never commit the `.env` file.

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

---

## Required

```env
# AEGIS backend API key — all non-public endpoints require this header: X-AEGIS-Key: <value>
# If not set, a random ephemeral key is generated at startup (insecure for production).
AEGIS_API_KEY=your-secret-key-here

# Postgres Database Credentials
POSTGRES_USER=aegis
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=your-secure-postgres-password
POSTGRES_DB=aegis_db

# Database URL used by AEGIS AI (matches Postgres credentials above)
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://${POSTGRES_USER}:${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}@postgres:5432/${POSTGRES_DB}
```

## Optional

```env
# Enable debug mode: exposes /docs, /openapi.json, X-Process-Time header
AEGIS_DEBUG=false

# Execution timeout for sandboxed commands (seconds, default: 5)
AEGIS_EXEC_TIMEOUT=5

# Maximum request body size in bytes (default: 5242880 = 5MB)
AEGIS_MAX_BODY_BYTES=5242880

# Colon-separated list of additional allowed executables in the kernel allowlist
# Example: AEGIS_ALLOWED_COMMANDS=node:ruff
AEGIS_ALLOWED_COMMANDS=

# Docker sandbox mode: set to "docker" to wrap execution in ephemeral containers
# Requires Docker daemon to be running
SANDBOX_MODE=subprocess

# VirusTotal API key for live IP reputation checks
# Get a free key at https://www.virustotal.com
VIRUSTOTAL_API_KEY=

# AI provider for semantic analysis
# Options: openai (default, requires OPENAI_API_KEY) | ollama (local, no key needed)
AI_PROVIDER=ollama
OPENAI_API_KEY=
```
